body:
I'm OK if you have some preference for not doing this, but I find the latter a lot easier to read while debugging/analysing output and there are loads of these due to case statement conversion.

Instead of:

```
if (a) {
  x;
} else {
  if (b) {
    y;
  } else {
    if (c) {
      z;
    } else {
      w;
    }
  }
}
```

Emit:

```
if (a) {
  x;
} else if (b) {
  y;
} else if (c) {
  z;
} else {
  w;
}
```
